last_episode_to_air.overview: The DNA results are revealed and Maggie sits down with Maura's family and reveals evidence released by law enforcement for the first time in 13-years.

name: The Disappearance of Maura Murray
overview: Explore the mysterious case of a 21-year-old nursing student who vanished 13 years ago without a trace, and the social media frenzy it sparked.

episodes.name: Everyone Has a Theory
episodes.overview: Journalist Maggie Freleng searches for answers in the 2004 disappearance of a nursing student following a car crash in New Hampshire...

episodes.name: A Reason to Run
episodes.overview: Maggie investigates reasons why Maura Murray secretly drove to New Hampshire and never came home, including a possible pregnancy or an emotional phone call with her sister.

episodes.name: After the Crash
episodes.overview: There are questions about happened to Maura after she crashed on a rural road in New Hampshire: did she run into the woods, hop into a car with someone she knew and escape to a new life in Canada, or worse, hitch a ride with a dangerous stranger.

episodes.name: Code of Silence
episodes.overview: New Hampshire's law enforcement community keeps their findings of Maura's case close to the chest; Maggie explores the theories related to a police conspiracy, hoping to break down a decade-long code of silence.

episodes.name: Something bad happened
episodes.overview: Killers and kidnappers are Maggie's focus as she works to find out if Maura Murray was the victim of foul play.

episodes.name: Summit
episodes.overview: The DNA results are revealed and Maggie sits down with Maura's family and reveals evidence released by law enforcement for the first time in 13-years.
